claim.claim-text:
9. A current sensor assembly comprising:
a conductor with a first flux concentrating recess and a second flux concentrating recess, wherein both flux concentrating recesses are located in general opposing positions about an outer surface of the conductor;
a first current sensor disposed in the first flux concentrating recess;
a second current sensor disposed in the second flux concentrating recess; and
an anti-differential processing configured to receive a signal from each current sensor indicative of a magnetic flux about a respective flux concentrating recess, the processor arranged to output an anti-differential value indicative of an amount of current in the conductor.

17. A method of manufacturing a current sensing system comprising the steps of:
providing a conductor configured to carry a current flow;
forming at least one pair of flux concentrating recesses in opposing positions about a periphery of the conductor;
disposing a current sensor in each flux concentrating recess;
configuring an anti-differential processing component to receive feedback from each of the current sensors; and
configuring the processing component to output an anti-differential value indicative of an amount of current flow in the conductor.
